Today, in São Paulo, the LGBT Parade takes place, one of the biggest manifestations in the world for respecting diversity.
Twenty years ago, demonstrators occupy Av. Paulista and show that it is possible to claim advances in a peaceful and democratic way.

It is worth mentioning that #SUS was a pioneer in recognizing the social name, guaranteeing dignity and inclusion to all.

One of the ministers of the interim government intends to overturn the decree, having signed the Draft Statute of the Executive Branch.

May the battle against all forms of intolerance and prejudice extend beyond the LGBT Parade. This is a constant task for everyone.
